response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: FizzBuzz Printer\", \"description\": \"Write a function `print_fizzbuzz` that takes an integer `n` as input and prints out the numbers from 1 to `n`, replacing multiples of 3 with 'Fizz', multiples of 5 with 'Buzz', and multiples of both with 'FizzBuzz'.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef print_fizzbuzz(n: int) -> None:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A positive integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Prints out the numbers from 1 to `n`, replacing multiples of 3 with 'Fizz', multiples of 5 with 'Buzz', and multiples of both with 'FizzBuzz'.\\n\", \"code\": \"def print_fizzbuzz(n: int) -> None:\\n    for i in range(1, n+1):\\n        if i % 3 == 0 and i % 5 == 0:\\n            print('FizzBuzz')\\n        elif i % 3 == 0:\\n            print('Fizz')\\n        elif i % 5 == 0:\\n            print('Buzz')\\n        else:\\n            print(i)\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert print_fizzbuzz(15) == None and print() == None\", \"assert list(print_fizzbuzz(10)) == ['1', '2', 'Fizz', '4', 'Buzz', 'Fizz', '7', '8', 'Fizz', 'Buzz', '11', 'Fizz', '13', '14', 'FizzBuzz']\", \"assert list(print_fizzbuzz(20)) == ['1', '2', 'Fizz', '4', 'Buzz', 'Fizz', '7', '8', 'Fizz', 'Buzz', '11', 'Fizz', '13', '14', 'FizzBuzz', '16', '17', 'Fizz', '19', 'Buzz', '20']\", \"assert list(print_fizzbuzz(3)) == ['1', '2', 'Fizz']\"] }"
